			Ft_ls

			PART 1

ls : List information about the FILEs (current directory by default)
     Sort entries alphabetically without flags

-l : Use a long listing format

-R, --recursive : List subdirectories recursively

-a, --all : Dot not igone entries startint with '.'

-r, --reverse : Reverse order while sorting

-t, --time : Sort by modification time, newest first

			BONUS

-u : Sort by acces time, newest first
     With -lt : sort by, and show access time
     With -l : show acces time and sort by name

-f : Dot not sort, enable -aU, disable -ls --colore

-g : Like -l, but do not list owner

-h, --human-readable : print human readable size

-S : Sort by file size, largest first

-G, --no-group : Don't print group names

-X : Sort alphabetically by entry extension

--author : print the autor of each file
     
